properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 15 at 2:06PM MST until February 17 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...SIGNIFICANT MOUNTAIN SNOWFALL EXPECTED SATURDAY NIGHT THROUGH
MONDAY...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches
with 8 to 10 inches possible in the highest peaks of the
northern Laramie Range. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Along and near the Laramie Range, along Pine Ridge in
Eastern Wyoming and the northern Nebraska Panhandle.

* WHEN...From 5 AM Sunday to 8 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Slick roads and reduced visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning and evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM SUNDAY TO 8 PM MST MONDAY
